# UI Migration Implementation Plan (Remaining Screens)

This plan details the strategy for migrating the remaining screens to the new `hc-` design system. We have successfully completed 11 files (Batch 1 and Batch 2). There are 68 `page.tsx` files in total. The screenshot tool captured 78 images, meaning some screens have multiple sub-states (like empty states, modals, or tab variations) that also need visual validation. Our goal is to complete all 68 source files, fulfilling the visual requirements for all 78 screenshots.

## User Review Required

> [!NOTE]
> Please review this comprehensive batch schedule. Once approved, I will begin executing the next batch (Batch 3). The batches have been organized by route module (Admin, Staff, Portal, Public) to ensure consistent components are developed and reused logically.

## Open Questions

> [!TIP]
> The screenshots tool captured 78 images but there are 68 `page.tsx` files. Are there any specific sub-states or interactions (like modals, nested tabs, or loading screens) you want me to pay special attention to while migrating the components?

## Proposed Changes

We will work systematically through the following batches. For each page, we will implement `PageHeader`, `DataPanel`, `KpiCard`, and other standardized components from our new design system while preserving existing forms, routes, and API logic.

